01:05:40,530 --> 01:05:41,784
Give me a moment
with Adrian.

1002
01:05:41,793 --> 01:05:43,996
No disrespect sir, we
do not have time.

1003
01:05:44,021 --> 01:05:47,329
Make time.

1004
01:05:57,309 --> 01:06:00,411
Did you ever meet
my wife: Dorothy?

1005
01:06:00,454 --> 01:06:04,235
No sir, I never had
that honor.

1006
01:06:04,324 --> 01:06:08,079
She was in and out
towards the end

1007
01:06:08,085 --> 01:06:10,235
The night before she
passed on, she took

1008
01:06:10,235 --> 01:06:12,083
my hand and told me:

1009
01:06:12,083 --> 01:06:16,454
"I think you should
have a lottery"

1010
01:06:16,490 --> 01:06:21,373
"Everyone should have
a chance to go"

1011
01:06:22,436 --> 01:06:26,512
Maybe that's what we
should have done.

1012
01:06:27,376 --> 01:06:32,302
I'll be the last president of
the United States of America.

1013
01:06:32,346 --> 01:06:35,222
Do you know how
that feels, son?

1014
01:06:35,380 --> 01:06:39,327
No one could have saved
the country, sir.

1015
01:06:39,577 --> 01:06:44,559
And I think, I think people
have a right to know.

1016
01:06:44,733 --> 01:06:48,255
Don't worry, I'll
take care of that.

1017
01:06:48,789 --> 01:06:51,737
Go on now.

1018
01:06:52,000 --> 01:06:54,235
Not without you, sir.

1019
01:06:56,001 --> 01:06:58,144
Get on that plane, son.

1020
01:06:58,161 --> 01:07:01,527
It's a brave new world
you head into

1021
01:07:01,545 --> 01:07:07,123
And a young scientist will
be worth 20 old politicians.

1022
01:07:24,215 --> 01:07:26,516
We should go to my parents
house in the Rockies.

1023
01:07:26,516 --> 01:07:29,382
This isn't one of your crazy
stories, now. Right, Jackson?

1024
01:07:29,382 --> 01:07:30,657
How the hell are we going
to make it to China?

1025
01:07:30,659 --> 01:07:31,692
Hey, Gordon.

1026
01:07:31,693 --> 01:07:33,876
Without Jackson we wouldn't
have made it out of California.

1027
01:07:33,923 --> 01:07:36,266
Noah, please.

1028
01:07:43,451 --> 01:07:45,351
Be careful with
the landing gear!

1029
01:07:45,371 --> 01:07:47,503
Easy gringo, I know
what I'm doing.

1030
01:07:47,505 --> 01:07:48,474
<i>Attention!</i>

1031
01:07:48,476 --> 01:07:50,483
<i>The National Guard
has informed us that an</i>

1032
01:07:50,485 --> 01:07:52,581
<i>extremely hazardous
ash cloud is headed for</i>

1033
01:07:52,581 --> 01:07:53,637
<i>the city of Las Vegas.</i>

1034
01:07:53,639 --> 01:07:55,347
Where are you going?

1035
01:07:57,427 --> 01:07:58,849
Move! You can't
stay here.

1036
01:07:58,849 --> 01:08:01,320
- I have a plane here.
- It's not safe.

1037
01:08:11,586 --> 01:08:15,112
So you got positive
confirmation on this?

1038
01:08:15,418 --> 01:08:18,336
Thank you,
I understand.

1039
01:08:27,377 --> 01:08:30,344
The President
is not coming.

1040
01:08:34,052 --> 01:08:39,809
So, the Captain won't
abandon his sinking ship.

1041
01:08:40,025 --> 01:08:43,422
That's his choice,
and a noble one.

1042
01:08:43,445 --> 01:08:45,242
I have also
just learned

1043
01:08:45,243 --> 01:08:47,398
that the Vice
President's chopper

1044
01:08:47,399 --> 01:08:50,823
went down in the ash
cloud outside Pittsburgh.

1045
01:08:51,032 --> 01:08:54,895
Fortunately, we have
protocols to follow.

1046
01:08:54,913 --> 01:08:56,284
What about the Speaker
of the House?

1047
01:08:56,286 --> 01:08:57,902
In this chaos, I have
no idea. Where is he?

1048
01:08:57,903 --> 01:08:59,488
He's the Commander
in Chief now, sir.

1049
01:08:59,489 --> 01:09:03,096
This is one flight he
shouldn't be late for.

1050
01:09:03,109 --> 01:09:04,399
Tell the Captain
we're taking off.

1051
01:09:04,400 --> 01:09:06,212
Sir, you don't have
the authority.

1052
01:09:06,212 --> 01:09:08,399
Who got the authority?
You? You got the authority?

1053
01:09:08,399 --> 01:09:10,268
You couldn't even keep
your damn mouth shut.

1054
01:09:10,269 --> 01:09:12,713
You betrayed top secret
information.

1055
01:09:12,729 --> 01:09:13,884
What the hell are
you talking about?

1056
01:09:13,885 --> 01:09:15,429
You told your father
everything,

1057
01:09:15,430 --> 01:09:16,889
put this entire
plan in jeopardy,

1058
01:09:16,890 --> 01:09:18,362
Good thing for you
the old man could

1059
01:09:18,396 --> 01:09:19,835
keep his mouth shut
better than you.

1060
01:09:19,836 --> 01:09:21,367
Don't look so shocked.

1061
01:09:21,368 --> 01:09:22,844
We had to monitor
everybody who knew,

1062
01:09:22,845 --> 01:09:24,654
How do you think we kept
it a secret for so long?

1063
01:09:24,655 --> 01:09:27,257
So you just killed anybody
who tried to talk?

1064
01:09:27,288 --> 01:09:29,836
Anybody who tried to talk
was not just an enemy

1065
01:09:29,837 --> 01:09:31,757
of the state. They were
an enemy of humanity.

1066
01:09:31,759 --> 01:09:33,987
The director of the Louvre
was an enemy of humanity?

1067
01:09:33,988 --> 01:09:36,664
After he called a press
conference he was.

1068
01:09:37,159 --> 01:09:39,150
Jesus, what did
you think?

1069
01:09:39,152 --> 01:09:40,323
We're all just gonna
get on board,

1070
01:09:40,323 --> 01:09:42,337
hold hands and
sing Kumbaya?

1071
01:09:43,197 --> 01:09:46,351
Sit down and
buckle up.

1072
01:09:54,203 --> 01:09:57,104
Excuse me, is my father
in the Command Center?

1073
01:09:57,127 --> 01:10:00,125
President is on
the line, Dr Wilson.

1074
01:10:00,557 --> 01:10:03,134
Thank you.

1075
01:10:08,413 --> 01:10:09,667
Where are you?

1076
01:10:09,710 --> 01:10:14,016
You never would've gotten
on that plane if I told you.

1077
01:10:15,422 --> 01:10:17,466
But you said that
you'd be here

1078
01:10:17,467 --> 01:10:19,019
Darling, listen to me.

1079
01:10:19,033 --> 01:10:21,798
Do you understand how
much strength it gives me

1080
01:10:21,800 --> 01:10:24,345
knowing that you
will survive?

1081
01:10:24,989 --> 01:10:28,443
The only thing left
to do now,

1082
01:10:28,463 --> 01:10:31,612
is tell the truth
to people.

1083
01:10:31,646 --> 01:10:36,234
At least if they know,

1084
01:10:36,235 --> 01:10:40,073
families can say
goodbye to each other.

1085
01:10:40,109 --> 01:10:44,274
A mother can comfort
her children.

1086
01:10:45,322 --> 01:10:49,157
And a father...

1087
01:10:49,158 --> 01:10:52,655
can ask his daughter
for forgiveness.

1088
01:11:00,470 --> 01:11:03,856
Whenever you're ready,
Mr President.

1089
01:11:10,702 --> 01:11:13,469
My fellow Americans

1090
01:11:13,698 --> 01:11:17,340
This will be the last
time I address you.

1091
01:11:17,578 --> 01:11:22,984
As you know, catastrophe
has struck our nation.

1092
01:11:23,867 --> 01:11:26,266
Has struck the world.

1093
01:11:26,268 --> 01:11:28,436
I wish I could tell you

1094
01:11:28,438 --> 01:11:31,679
we could prevent
the coming destruction.

1095
01:11:31,694 --> 01:11:33,492
We cannot.

1096
01:11:33,840 --> 01:11:37,376
Today, none of us
are strangers.

1097
01:11:37,618 --> 01:11:40,849
Today, we are
one family,

1098
01:11:40,867 --> 01:11:44,179
stepping into the
darkness together.

1099
01:11:44,202 --> 01:11:47,243
We are a nation of
many religions,

1100
01:11:47,268 --> 01:11:51,135
but I believe these
words reflect the spirit

1101
01:11:51,136 --> 01:11:53,412
of all our faiths:

1102
01:11:53,662 --> 01:11:56,488
"The lord is my
Shepard. I shall... "

1103
01:11:58,306 --> 01:12:01,640
People! Get away from
the doors and windows.

1104
01:12:01,881 --> 01:12:04,282
What are we gonna do?
You tell me.

1105
01:12:04,317 --> 01:12:07,125
- Dr Silberman?
- Tamara!

1106
01:12:07,126 --> 01:12:09,342
What are you
doing here?

1107
01:12:09,344 --> 01:12:10,610
She's a patient,
Honey.

1108
01:12:10,628 --> 01:12:14,078
Excuse me, I have a
private plane out there.

1109
01:12:14,078 --> 01:12:17,195
Karpov! Yuri!

1110
01:12:17,197 --> 01:12:19,349
You knew. This whole
time you knew.

1111
01:12:19,384 --> 01:12:21,822
You've got a way out of here,
right? You got a plane?

1112
01:12:21,845 --> 01:12:24,350
My family, take us
with you. Please!

1113
01:12:24,368 --> 01:12:26,637
Boss, boss.

1114
01:12:26,639 --> 01:12:28,408
I found us a plane.
An Antonov.

1115
01:12:28,409 --> 01:12:29,667
They were just
about to take off,

1116
01:12:29,668 --> 01:12:31,146
but the tower
didn't let them.

1117
01:12:31,148 --> 01:12:34,287
Can you still fly
that thing?

1118
01:12:34,322 --> 01:12:37,426
Sure, Boss, but
I need co-pilot.

1119
01:12:37,447 --> 01:12:40,256
Gordon's a pilot.

1120
01:12:40,256 --> 01:12:42,070
No, I'm not.

1121
01:12:42,072 --> 01:12:44,740
Yes he is. Great pilot.
Let's go.

1122
01:12:44,756 --> 01:12:47,429
Good. Let's go!

1123
01:12:47,454 --> 01:12:51,506
Jackson, stop
saying I'm a pilot.

1124
01:12:51,533 --> 01:12:54,640
You can't go out there.
Come back!

1125
01:12:58,873 --> 01:13:01,194
Move back, people!

1126
01:13:06,645 --> 01:13:09,162
Wow, that's
a big plane.

1127
01:13:09,557 --> 01:13:12,085
It's Russian.

1128
01:13:12,159 --> 01:13:14,144
Let's move everybody.
Come on!

1129
01:13:18,970 --> 01:13:21,457
- Gordon, where are you?
- Let's go!

1130
01:13:21,480 --> 01:13:24,663
Up here, Gordon.
Hurry up!

1131
01:13:24,851 --> 01:13:27,395
Oh my God.

1132
01:13:34,350 --> 01:13:37,831
- Woah, look at these.
- Las Vegas auto show.

1133
01:13:37,841 --> 01:13:40,953
We had VIP tickets
for this.

1134
01:13:40,975 --> 01:13:42,279
That's fantastic, let's go.

1135
01:13:42,307 --> 01:13:44,134
Check the main bus
for hydraulics,

1136
01:13:44,135 --> 01:13:45,287
I'll balance the tanks.

1137
01:13:45,322 --> 01:13:47,387
What?

1138
01:13:47,878 --> 01:13:50,046
Okay, okay.
I'm trying.

1139
01:13:52,135 --> 01:13:54,126
Tower to Antonov, what
the hell are you doing?

1140
01:13:54,127 --> 01:13:55,086
Shut down immediately.

1141
01:14:02,789 --> 01:14:03,898
- Caesar, shh.

1142
01:14:04,444 --> 01:14:05,480
When I say "go"

1143
01:14:05,481 --> 01:14:07,377
we push all this down
at once, okay?

1144
01:14:07,396 --> 01:14:08,938
- Okay.
- Go!

1145
01:14:08,970 --> 01:14:12,987
Antonov, abort take-off.
You do not have clearance.

1146
01:14:13,024 --> 01:14:16,570
I repeat, you
must abort.

1147
01:14:21,532 --> 01:14:22,676
What the hell
was that?

1148
01:14:22,676 --> 01:14:25,067
I don't know, but
it's not good.

1149
01:14:27,185 --> 01:14:30,319
- Push!
- Pushing! Come on!

1150
01:14:33,413 --> 01:14:35,840
We're going down!

1151
01:14:44,051 --> 01:14:46,331
It must be the...
Take over.

1152
01:14:46,364 --> 01:14:49,177
What do you mean,
take over?

1153
01:14:50,851 --> 01:14:52,863
- Sasha!
- Relax.

1154
01:14:52,894 --> 01:14:54,514
Now!

1155
01:14:58,948 --> 01:14:59,807
Jesus.

1156
01:15:02,720 --> 01:15:04,421
- Oh God
- I think I got it

1157
01:15:04,453 --> 01:15:07,315
- Sasha, now!
- Take a deep breath.

1158
01:15:07,912 --> 01:15:09,301
Pull!

1159
01:15:34,894 --> 01:15:37,332
Was that the Eiffel Tower?

1160
01:15:37,472 --> 01:15:41,164
I think so.

1161
01:15:46,307 --> 01:15:51,998
Ladies and Gentlemen.
We're on our way to China.

1162
01:15:52,318 --> 01:15:57,324
Good. Very good.

1163
01:16:04,752 --> 01:16:06,868
Do not believe in
something simply

1164
01:16:06,868 --> 01:16:09,891
because you have
heard it, Nima.

1165
01:16:09,893 --> 01:16:13,604
But great Lama.
Tenzin is my brother.

1166
01:16:13,661 --> 01:16:15,090
He works inside
the big tunnel,

1167
01:16:15,091 --> 01:16:16,931
where the ships
are built.

1168
01:16:19,328 --> 01:16:22,154
But what is there
in your wisdom,

1169
01:16:22,154 --> 01:16:24,479
great Lama,
if Tenzin is right?

1170
01:16:24,480 --> 01:16:28,686
What if our world is
indeed coming to and end?

1171
01:16:36,453 --> 01:16:39,854
It is full, great Rinpoche.

1172
01:16:45,020 --> 01:16:46,413
Like this cup,

1173
01:16:46,457 --> 01:16:52,213
you are full of opinions and
speculations.

1174
01:16:52,577 --> 01:16:54,560
To see the light
of wisdom,

1175
01:16:54,601 --> 01:16:58,771
You first must
empty your cup.

1176
01:17:14,106 --> 01:17:16,000
Be careful with
the clutch...

1177
01:17:16,360 --> 01:17:18,668
It tends to slip.

1178
01:17:37,350 --> 01:17:39,304
Grandpa, Nima is here!

1179
01:17:39,337 --> 01:17:41,092
Grandma, I got a message
from Tenzin...

1180
01:17:41,127 --> 01:17:43,097
He want us to meet
him in Cho Ming

1181
01:17:43,099 --> 01:17:44,057
at the work camp.

1182
01:17:45,443 --> 01:17:48,043
He says he can get us onto
the ships he's working on.

1183
01:17:48,045 --> 01:17:49,865
What are you
talking about?

1184
01:17:49,867 --> 01:17:52,345
Tenzin works
on the dam.

1185
01:17:54,841 --> 01:17:56,221
Grandma...

1186
01:17:56,867 --> 01:18:00,166
...the dam is a ship.
The government lied to us.

1187
01:18:00,863 --> 01:18:02,722
There will be a big flood!

1188
01:18:03,372 --> 01:18:04,993
We must pack up
right away.

1189
01:18:05,158 --> 01:18:07,926
Nima? Who gave
you a truck?

1190
01:18:08,621 --> 01:18:11,774
We took a trip on the
Liam Song ferry once

1191
01:18:11,898 --> 01:18:14,521
Grandpa threw up
the whole way.

1192
01:18:15,479 --> 01:18:17,345
Let's eat first.

1193
01:18:21,962 --> 01:18:25,481
Hey, look, the new Bentley!
Our father had one on order.

1194
01:18:25,903 --> 01:18:27,814
He was supposed to
get it next year.

1195
01:18:27,814 --> 01:18:30,640
But then he canceled it.
Because of the ships.

1196
01:18:31,314 --> 01:18:33,359
How many cars does
your family have?

1197
01:18:33,394 --> 01:18:36,376
My mom's boyfriend
has a Porsche.

1198
01:18:37,359 --> 01:18:39,530
Our parents are
divorced too.

1199
01:18:41,708 --> 01:18:43,282
Found a hat.

1200
01:18:43,573 --> 01:18:45,596
She has a thing
for hats.

1201
01:18:45,597 --> 01:18:47,873
I was just like
that at her age.

1202
01:18:48,261 --> 01:18:50,157
They made me
feel safe.

1203
01:18:50,765 --> 01:18:54,069
So, how did you meet
Dr Silberman?

1204
01:18:55,061 --> 01:18:57,399
As you can see not the
same way you did.

1205
01:18:58,905 --> 01:19:02,560
My boyfriend asked me
to get them done

1206
01:19:02,702 --> 01:19:04,528
But he's not
your husband?

1207
01:19:04,899 --> 01:19:06,492
We are not married.

1208
01:19:06,493 --> 01:19:08,623
And probably
never will be.

1209
01:19:15,770 --> 01:19:17,625
For the boys.

1210
01:19:21,470 --> 01:19:24,827
They seem to like
each other.

1211
01:19:26,367 --> 01:19:27,931
Yeah, I guess.

1212
01:19:29,158 --> 01:19:32,128
Tell me, Mr Karpov,
how much did you pay?

1213
01:19:32,207 --> 01:19:36,600
One billion Euro.
Per seat.

1214
01:19:37,984 --> 01:19:40,582
That's disgusting
- Oh yeah?

1215
01:19:41,380 --> 01:19:45,356
You know, Curtis, I wasn't
always a businessman.

1216
01:19:45,466 --> 01:19:47,650
I am a boxer.

1217
01:19:47,652 --> 01:19:49,662
Was my only playing
when I was boy

1218
01:19:49,662 --> 01:19:52,645
back in Murmansk.
And my coach,

1219
01:19:52,680 --> 01:19:57,451
his name was also Yuri.
He always said:

1220
01:19:57,485 --> 01:20:00,935
"If someone wants
to beat you...

1221
01:20:00,935 --> 01:20:03,707
...he has to
kill you first"

1222
01:20:06,681 --> 01:20:09,649
That's very nice.

1223
01:20:10,114 --> 01:20:12,704
But tell me, what
would you have done

1224
01:20:12,739 --> 01:20:15,592
if you were rich
like me?

1225
01:20:15,594 --> 01:20:18,728
Look, they are
wonderful children.

1226
01:20:20,122 --> 01:20:23,313
OK guys. The plan is
to refill in Hawaii,

1227
01:20:23,314 --> 01:20:25,460
so sit down and
buckle up.

1228
01:20:25,461 --> 01:20:28,588
Gordon and I
will do the rest.

1229
01:20:29,932 --> 01:20:31,557
Oh God.

1230
01:20:32,966 --> 01:20:34,773
Go get the guys.

1231
01:20:37,171 --> 01:20:42,353
Guys, there's a...
You might wanna...

1232
01:20:58,052 --> 01:21:02,600
- What is that?
- The state of Hawaii

1233
01:21:03,023 --> 01:21:06,983
Not good. That is
not good.

1234
01:21:11,594 --> 01:21:13,378
How much fuel do
we have left?

1235
01:21:13,380 --> 01:21:14,514
Not enough.

1236
01:21:14,515 --> 01:21:16,734
We have to make a
water landing

1237
01:21:16,734 --> 01:21:18,631
Somewhere in
South China sea.

1238
01:21:18,743 --> 01:21:21,773
Great, at least we won't
need a landing gear.

1239
01:21:21,807 --> 01:21:24,802
- What about it?
- We lost it all, in Vegas.

1240
01:21:34,871 --> 01:21:36,923
Dr Wilson,
may I come in?

1241
01:21:37,480 --> 01:21:39,850
I'm not very good
company, I'm afraid.

1242
01:21:40,817 --> 01:21:43,823
- Doctor...
- Please, call me Adrian.

1243
01:21:49,157 --> 01:21:51,585
All those people
we left behind.

1244
01:21:51,952 --> 01:21:54,649
They don't stand
a chance, do they?

1245
01:21:55,797 --> 01:21:58,661
I believe that nature
will choose for itself,

1246
01:21:58,662 --> 01:22:01,746
from itself, what
will survive.

1247
01:22:02,457 --> 01:22:06,228
Just like you, preserving
those great artworks.

1248
