01:46:14,877 --> 01:46:16,565
These people were chosen
by geneticists?

1501
01:46:16,567 --> 01:46:18,518
<i>All green card holders</i>

1502
01:46:18,519 --> 01:46:20,261
<i>Please proceed to
hangar D-4</i>

1503
01:46:20,261 --> 01:46:22,197
Looks to me like their check
books got them on board.

1504
01:46:22,231 --> 01:46:24,131
That's right, Dr Wilson.
Without billions of dollars

1505
01:46:24,167 --> 01:46:26,270
from the private sector
this entire operation

1506
01:46:26,271 --> 01:46:27,231
would've been
impossible.

1507
01:46:27,488 --> 01:46:28,693
We sold tickets?

1508
01:46:29,618 --> 01:46:30,630
What about all
these workers?

1509
01:46:31,390 --> 01:46:32,685
They all get passes?

1510
01:46:33,208 --> 01:46:35,628
What? Life isn't fair?

1511
01:46:35,904 --> 01:46:36,659
Is that it?

1512
01:46:37,081 --> 01:46:38,498
If you want to
donate your passes,

1513
01:46:38,500 --> 01:46:41,802
to a couple of Chinese
workers, be my guest.

1514
01:46:42,462 --> 01:46:43,828
Captain, I want a
pre-launch briefing.

1515
01:46:43,829 --> 01:46:45,672
All international
teams present.

1516
01:47:19,356 --> 01:47:21,162
What the hell?

1517
01:47:24,235 --> 01:47:27,118
What is this? They could've
fit 10 people in here.

1518
01:47:33,921 --> 01:47:35,243
Satnam, where are you?

1519
01:47:35,792 --> 01:47:38,394
- On the Nampan Plateau.
- What?

1520
01:47:40,252 --> 01:47:42,613
There's a tidal wave
coming from the east.

1521
01:47:42,613 --> 01:47:43,765
It's gigantic.

1522
01:47:44,132 --> 01:47:45,676
<i>Satnam, what
happened?</i>

1523
01:47:45,676 --> 01:47:47,470
We never got
picked up, Adrian.

1524
01:47:47,470 --> 01:47:49,658
The airlift
never came.

1525
01:47:51,448 --> 01:47:52,859
Goodbye, my friend.

1526
01:47:53,890 --> 01:47:56,557
Satnam

1527
01:48:21,770 --> 01:48:23,938
- Where are we set up?
- Over there.

1528
01:48:28,554 --> 01:48:31,242
Give me the satellite
images from Napam, India.

1529
01:48:31,654 --> 01:48:32,306
What's happening?

1530
01:48:33,478 --> 01:48:36,078
Satnam was talking
about another wave,

1531
01:48:36,078 --> 01:48:37,613
coming from the east.

1532
01:48:41,059 --> 01:48:42,324
- Holy mother of God.

1533
01:48:42,326 --> 01:48:44,595
So the flooding
will hit earlier?

1534
01:48:44,596 --> 01:48:46,302
The second wave
is closer?

1535
01:48:46,304 --> 01:48:47,381
Plug in the new data.

1536
01:48:49,152 --> 01:48:50,707
Satnam didn't
get picked up.

1537
01:48:50,707 --> 01:48:51,667
What?

1538
01:48:51,886 --> 01:48:54,412
A lot of people didn't get
picked up in this chaos.

1539
01:48:54,722 --> 01:48:56,730
This is not a conspiracy,
Helmsley.

1540
01:48:56,731 --> 01:48:58,045
Your predictions haven't
exactly panned out,

1541
01:48:58,046 --> 01:48:59,603
have they, Doctor?

1542
01:48:59,604 --> 01:49:01,837
It's ready.

1543
01:49:03,421 --> 01:49:05,640
Oh God, its 1500
meters high.

1544
01:49:06,716 --> 01:49:08,113
When will it
get here?

1545
01:49:08,649 --> 01:49:09,728
Talk to me, Hemsley,
when will it hit?

1546
01:49:09,729 --> 01:49:11,886
Adjust the countdown.

1547
01:49:27,069 --> 01:49:30,256
28 minutes, 10 seconds
to impact.

1548
01:49:30,256 --> 01:49:31,034
My God.

1549
01:49:31,436 --> 01:49:33,235
Captain.

1550
01:49:33,237 --> 01:49:35,082
I need to speak to the
other heads of state.

1551
01:49:35,083 --> 01:49:36,493
- Right away. Taylor?
- Aye, Captain

1552
01:49:36,493 --> 01:49:39,930
Standing by. Ark 6, stand by.
Ark 7, stand by.

1553
01:49:39,965 --> 01:49:42,603
This is Carl Anheuser
acting CIC on 4,

1554
01:49:42,604 --> 01:49:43,208
Yes sir

1555
01:49:43,210 --> 01:49:45,282
Requesting emergency
conference T-99.

1556
01:50:05,296 --> 01:50:06,996
He thinks the world of
you, you know that?

1557
01:50:09,560 --> 01:50:11,421
He's a great little man.

1558
01:50:12,158 --> 01:50:13,244
Yeah

1559
01:50:21,240 --> 01:50:23,118
I always wanted to have
a family of my own.

1560
01:50:27,063 --> 01:50:28,725
You're a lucky
man, Jackson.

1561
01:50:30,088 --> 01:50:31,393
Don't ever forget it.

1562
01:50:33,521 --> 01:50:35,273
CHO MING UTILITY GATE

1563
01:50:47,101 --> 01:50:48,149
Who are they?

1564
01:50:48,610 --> 01:50:50,282
We found them alongside
of the road.

1565
01:50:50,283 --> 01:50:52,234
Send them back!

1566
01:50:57,801 --> 01:50:59,479
I am a follower

1567
01:51:00,226 --> 01:51:02,203
of our great
Lama Rinpoche.

1568
01:51:02,902 --> 01:51:04,311
You know I cannot do that.

1569
01:51:05,757 --> 01:51:07,255
You don't have to
take all of us.

1570
01:51:07,256 --> 01:51:08,344
Please just take
my children.

1571
01:51:08,345 --> 01:51:09,592
I'm begging you.

1572
01:51:09,988 --> 01:51:11,547
Why should
I do that?

1573
01:51:11,548 --> 01:51:15,453
Same reason you
sent for your family.

1574
01:51:15,890 --> 01:51:18,363
Please just the children,
you don't have to take us.

1575
01:51:18,363 --> 01:51:19,323
Please!

1576
01:51:21,960 --> 01:51:25,154
Please. Oh my God.

1577
01:51:27,707 --> 01:51:31,390
Please. I don't know if you can
understand what I'm saying.

1578
01:51:31,391 --> 01:51:33,966
As a mother,
I'm begging you.

1579
01:51:33,967 --> 01:51:35,408
Please take them.

1580
01:51:36,666 --> 01:51:37,646
Please.

1581
01:51:40,033 --> 01:51:43,239
We are all children
of the Earth.

1582
01:51:44,029 --> 01:51:47,359
My plan will not work
for so many, Grandma.

1583
01:51:47,360 --> 01:51:51,139
We will take them all.

1584
01:52:05,675 --> 01:52:09,725
Attention.
All construction workers.

1585
01:52:12,318 --> 01:52:14,188
They're opening
the mountain.

1586
01:52:14,189 --> 01:52:17,371
They are leaving
without us.

1587
01:52:18,485 --> 01:52:20,211
Get back. What did
I tell you!

1588
01:52:20,212 --> 01:52:24,056
They are leaving
you behind too.

1589
01:52:24,057 --> 01:52:25,328
<i>Please be patient</i>

1590
01:52:36,996 --> 01:52:39,233
Follow me.

1591
01:52:45,292 --> 01:52:46,728
We have to hurry!

1592
01:52:46,729 --> 01:52:47,997
They are leaving!

1593
01:52:50,648 --> 01:52:52,994
Initiating security
procedures.

1594
01:52:58,167 --> 01:53:00,743
Excuse me. Where can I
find Adrian Helmsley?

1595
01:53:00,744 --> 01:53:02,082
He's on the bridge.
This way.

1596
01:53:06,158 --> 01:53:07,335
Tenzin wait!

1597
01:53:08,667 --> 01:53:10,608
Grandma, we're
almost there.

1598
01:53:10,801 --> 01:53:12,740
Green lights on
pressure, Mr Anton?

1599
01:53:12,742 --> 01:53:14,506
Green lights across
the board, Captain.

1600
01:53:26,144 --> 01:53:27,340
Why do they
have anchors?

1601
01:53:27,341 --> 01:53:30,382
Because they're not
space ships. They're Arcs.

1602
01:53:30,845 --> 01:53:31,949
Let's go.

1603
01:53:43,891 --> 01:53:45,248
Mr President.

1604
01:53:46,237 --> 01:53:47,213
You've got to see this.

1605
01:54:16,679 --> 01:54:18,823
Stop.

1606
01:54:26,817 --> 01:54:28,310
Engage the support
mechanisms.

1607
01:54:28,310 --> 01:54:30,905
Aye-aye, Captain.
Engaging supports.

1608
01:54:30,907 --> 01:54:32,130
Just exactly how long
are these things

1609
01:54:32,131 --> 01:54:33,655
expected to hold us
in place, Captain?

1610
01:54:33,657 --> 01:54:34,519
They're just meant
to withstand the

1611
01:54:34,520 --> 01:54:37,351
first impact of the
waves, Mr Anheuser.

1612
01:54:53,895 --> 01:54:56,739
Down there Oleg,
you go first.

1613
01:55:01,789 --> 01:55:02,985
Caesar!

1614
01:55:22,900 --> 01:55:26,185
Good boy.
Come to Mommy.

1615
01:55:26,186 --> 01:55:27,239
Caesar!

1616
01:55:27,974 --> 01:55:30,025
Mommy, where's Tamara?

1617
01:55:32,228 --> 01:55:33,936
Daddy look!

1618
01:55:36,667 --> 01:55:38,350
Tamara!

1619
01:56:13,351 --> 01:56:16,780
Oh my god, what's
happening out there?

1620
01:56:17,530 --> 01:56:20,628
Anheuser convinced the other
heads of state to launch.

1621
01:56:23,845 --> 01:56:25,420
Mr. Anheuser

1622
01:56:27,069 --> 01:56:29,011
We have to stop
this madness.

1623
01:56:29,798 --> 01:56:31,722
Make sure the other
bridges can see me.

1624
01:56:32,515 --> 01:56:33,091
What do you think
you're doing?

1625
01:56:33,091 --> 01:56:34,457
I know exactly
what I'm doing.

1626
01:56:37,030 --> 01:56:39,029
Ladies and Gentleman,
this is Dr. Adrian Helmsley

1627
01:56:39,032 --> 01:56:42,110
Chief science adviser to
the late President Wilson.

1628
01:56:42,212 --> 01:56:44,871
Could you please turn up
the volume, Mr Hoffman.

1629
01:56:45,061 --> 01:56:46,069
I know we've all
been forced to make

1630
01:56:46,070 --> 01:56:49,274
difficult decisions to save
our human civilization.

1631
01:56:49,274 --> 01:56:51,967
But to be human means
to care for each other

1632
01:56:52,002 --> 01:56:53,972
and civilization means
to work together

1633
01:56:53,974 --> 01:56:55,908
to create a better life.

1634
01:56:56,041 --> 01:56:58,261
If that's true, then
there's nothing human

1635
01:56:58,261 --> 01:57:01,234
and nothing civilized about
what we're doing here.

1636
01:57:01,235 --> 01:57:03,728
Dr. Helmsley's passion
is admirable,

1637
01:57:03,862 --> 01:57:06,453
But I remind you that
we have very limited

1638
01:57:06,454 --> 01:57:08,158
resources and extremely
limited time.

1639
01:57:08,159 --> 01:57:09,854
Ask yourselves, can
we really stand by

1640
01:57:09,855 --> 01:57:12,957
and watch these
people die?

1641
01:57:13,345 --> 01:57:15,362
I read a quote
two days ago.

1642
01:57:15,465 --> 01:57:17,698
The author is probably
dead by now. But he said:

1643
01:57:17,698 --> 01:57:20,073
"The moment we stop
fighting for each other"

1644
01:57:20,078 --> 01:57:23,378
"Thats the moment that
we lose our humanity"

1645
01:57:23,465 --> 01:57:24,654
And in order to save
the human race,

1646
01:57:24,655 --> 01:57:27,162
we have and obligation
to stick to this plan

1647
01:57:27,198 --> 01:57:30,288
which every nation on this
flotilla signed up for.

1648
01:57:30,289 --> 01:57:32,649
They're in God's
hands now.

1649
01:57:34,432 --> 01:57:36,842
Officer, you turn that off.

1650
01:57:37,791 --> 01:57:38,958
That is an order,
sailor. Turn it off!

1651
01:57:38,993 --> 01:57:40,673
Don't you dare touch
that button, young man!

1652
01:57:40,675 --> 01:57:43,488
Have you completely
lost your mind?

1653
01:57:43,815 --> 01:57:44,734
Look at the clock!

1654
01:57:44,913 --> 01:57:47,372
We have barely
15 minutes left!

1655
01:57:47,646 --> 01:57:48,394
Do you want to be
responsible for the

1656
01:57:48,395 --> 01:57:49,966
extinction of the
human race?

1657
01:57:49,966 --> 01:57:51,367
Can you handle
that, Adrian?

1658
01:57:52,023 --> 01:57:54,167
There's a young astrophysicist
from India who's the

1659
01:57:54,168 --> 01:57:55,345
reason we are all here.

1660
01:57:55,345 --> 01:57:56,993
Oh, for God's sake.

1661
01:57:57,145 --> 01:57:59,583
He's the one who
discovered it all.

1662
01:57:59,585 --> 01:58:03,164
He connected all the dots,
we all owe him our lives.

1663
01:58:03,268 --> 01:58:04,556
I just learned that
he was killed with

1664
01:58:04,557 --> 01:58:08,480
his family in a Tsunami
in eastern India.

1665
01:58:09,987 --> 01:58:12,177
He was my friend.

1666
01:58:12,775 --> 01:58:15,009
And he died in vain.

1667
01:58:15,341 --> 01:58:18,372
Everybody out there
has died in vain.

1668
01:58:18,515 --> 01:58:22,385
If we start our future
with an act of cruelty,

1669
01:58:23,671 --> 01:58:28,932
what will you tell
your children?

1670
01:58:31,273 --> 01:58:35,180
If my father were here,
he would open the gates

1671
01:58:41,644 --> 01:58:44,162
The people of Russia
along with...

1672
01:58:45,175 --> 01:58:46,435
China

1673
01:58:48,212 --> 01:58:49,948
and Japan

1674
01:58:49,948 --> 01:58:50,908
Agree

1675
01:58:52,247 --> 01:58:54,488
To open the gates!

1676
01:58:55,884 --> 01:59:00,112
The United Kingdom, Spain,
France and Germany,

1677
01:59:00,115 --> 01:59:02,453
and I believe I may
also speak for the

1678
01:59:02,454 --> 01:59:04,381
Italian Prime Minister:

1679
01:59:04,645 --> 01:59:08,305
We vote to let these
people come in.

1680
01:59:13,095 --> 01:59:15,248
Captain Michaels.

1681
01:59:16,225 --> 01:59:18,800
Please

1682
01:59:21,055 --> 01:59:22,613
This is your Captain.

1683
01:59:22,613 --> 01:59:26,072
In a few moments,
we will open the gates.

1684
01:59:32,940 --> 01:59:35,615
Phew, it stinks.

1685
01:59:53,380 --> 01:59:55,689
They are opening
the gate. Come down!

1686
01:59:55,690 --> 01:59:57,551
Noah. Move it!

1687
01:59:58,074 --> 02:00:00,717
Noah! Noah!

1688
02:00:11,011 --> 02:00:13,012
Mom, something happened.

1689
02:00:20,399 --> 02:00:22,828
Come on, God damn it!
Give me your hand!

1690
02:00:22,829 --> 02:00:26,658
- Reach for it!
- Help me!

1691
02:00:29,009 --> 02:00:31,018
Gordon!

1692
02:00:32,856 --> 02:00:34,503
Stop!

1693
02:00:39,095 --> 02:00:40,578
Climb!

1694
02:01:12,960 --> 02:01:14,190
What's wrong
with the gate?

1695
02:01:14,511 --> 02:01:15,550
Looks like it didn't
run the full cycle.

1696
02:01:15,551 --> 02:01:16,511
We're checking it out.

1697
02:01:18,135 --> 02:01:21,091
Order, please!

1698
02:01:25,326 --> 02:01:28,269
<i>4 minutes to impact</i>

1699
02:02:11,863 --> 02:02:14,881
We're all loaded, Captain.
Then let's lock it up. Now!

1700
02:02:24,426 --> 02:02:27,673
Oleg! Grab
my hand!

1701
02:02:39,109 --> 02:02:45,344
No, no, no

1702
02:02:56,759 --> 02:02:58,087
HYDRAULIC MALFUNCTION

1703
02:02:58,283 --> 02:02:59,863
Something's jamming the
hydraulics, Captain.

1704
02:03:00,003 --> 02:03:01,115
Well then get it out
for Christ sake.

1705
02:03:01,117 --> 02:03:02,462
I can't fire up the
engines until we

1706
02:03:02,463 --> 02:03:03,900
get a good seal
on that gate.

1707
02:03:04,757 --> 02:03:07,099
Captain, we have a breach
in the zoological bay.

1708
02:03:07,243 --> 02:03:09,268
Can you zoom in?
- Yeah.

1709
02:03:13,293 --> 02:03:14,237
I know those kids.

1710
02:03:14,238 --> 02:03:16,679
What is happening?
What's going on?

1711
02:03:16,908 --> 02:03:18,672
Where did they
come from?

1712
02:03:20,461 --> 02:03:22,400
There. Through the
hydraulic chamber.

1713
02:03:22,529 --> 02:03:23,783
Captain, I think we
found the problem!

1714
02:03:23,784 --> 02:03:26,270
- Who are these people?
- No, wait!

1715
02:03:26,676 --> 02:03:27,466
He's injured.

1716
02:03:27,832 --> 02:03:31,403
Something must've
gone wrong.

1717
02:03:31,438 --> 02:03:34,244
Are you kidding me? Of course
something went wrong!

1718
02:03:34,256 --> 02:03:36,060
Congratulations to
the both of you.

1719
02:03:36,125 --> 02:03:37,295
Might have gotten us
all killed, but as long

1720
02:03:37,296 --> 02:03:39,461
as your conscience is
clean, right Helmsley?

1721
02:03:39,462 --> 02:03:41,430
Captain, get an emergency
team down there,

1722
02:03:41,430 --> 02:03:43,113
I'll meet them at the
hydraulics chamber.

1723
02:03:43,114 --> 02:03:44,983
You know your way
around here? Lets go!

1724
02:03:45,119 --> 02:03:47,354
<i>1 minute to impact.</i>

1725
02:04:00,344 --> 02:04:01,083
Captain?

1726
02:04:01,552 --> 02:04:03,480
Cho Ming airfield
has been hit.

1727
02:04:03,800 --> 02:04:07,694
Put me on emergency
comm, Mr Taylor.

1728
02:04:08,154 --> 02:04:10,278
This is the Captain speaking

1729
02:04:10,338 --> 02:04:13,010
We expect to be impacted
by water shortly.

1730
02:04:13,202 --> 02:04:17,951
We need to
go this way.

1731
02:04:35,003 --> 02:04:38,136
All stations prepare
for impact.

1732
02:05:21,885 --> 02:05:24,296
Pressure just climbed
80 Pascal.

1733
02:05:24,298 --> 02:05:27,024
Surface compression of
valve sensors, Captain.

1734
02:05:27,025 --> 02:05:29,377
Track Dr Helmsley.

1735
02:05:34,012 --> 02:05:36,818
Out of the way!
Excuse me.

1736
02:05:37,511 --> 02:05:39,734
Tenzin. Almost there.

1737
02:05:40,381 --> 02:05:42,046
Nima. What happened?

1738
02:05:44,042 --> 02:05:44,944
Tamara!

1739
02:05:44,944 --> 02:05:47,286
Will you take
the kids please?

1740
02:05:47,604 --> 02:05:48,707
Which way?

1741
02:05:48,890 --> 02:05:52,930
We can't get there!
Water is entering the stern.

1742
02:05:52,963 --> 02:05:55,094
The rear of this ship is
flooded and will seal up

1743
02:05:55,113 --> 02:05:56,667
one compartment
at a time.

1744
02:05:57,000 --> 02:05:58,457
Where's Gordon?

1745
02:05:59,721 --> 02:06:00,734
No?

1746
02:06:02,675 --> 02:06:04,828
We gotta go back!

1747
02:06:04,829 --> 02:06:06,462
We have to go back!

1748
02:06:09,890 --> 02:06:11,078
Mommy!

1749
02:06:12,018 --> 02:06:13,427
Help!
Mommy!

1750
02:06:15,819 --> 02:06:18,371
Run!

1751
02:06:21,948 --> 02:06:25,509
Go over, Lilly!

1752
02:06:26,323 --> 02:06:28,662
Caesar!
Lilly, take him!

1753
02:06:30,757 --> 02:06:32,824
Mommy!

1754
02:06:39,530 --> 02:06:41,780
Is there another way to
the hydraulics chamber?

1755
02:06:41,997 --> 02:06:42,914
Where does this ladder go?

1756
02:06:42,949 --> 02:06:45,931
- To the zoological pens
- Okay, let's go!

1757
02:06:51,565 --> 02:06:54,954
Professor?
It's Air Force One.

1758
02:07:11,400 --> 02:07:13,163
The mid-ship anchor
support is hit.

1759
02:07:13,243 --> 02:07:14,243
Can you stabilize it?

1760
02:07:14,244 --> 02:07:16,012
The bow anchor
is giving in.

1761
02:07:34,661 --> 02:07:36,650
Captain, the turbines
aren't responding.

1762
02:07:36,652 --> 02:07:39,564
So override it.
Hit the override.

1763
02:07:39,597 --> 02:07:41,332
We cant start the engine
until we close that gate.

1764
02:07:58,960 --> 02:08:01,356
Help me!
Help!

1765
02:08:06,418 --> 02:08:10,261
Momma!

1766
02:08:10,295 --> 02:08:12,050
- Are you OK?
- My mommy is in there.

1767
02:08:12,051 --> 02:08:13,011
Please help her!

1768
02:08:13,011 --> 02:08:13,836
We'll get to your
mommy, sweetheart.

1769
02:08:13,837 --> 02:08:15,548
They're doing everything
they can, okay?

1770
02:08:15,550 --> 02:08:16,667
Can we talk to her?

1771
02:08:16,702 --> 02:08:18,667
I'm gonna try
to connect us.

1772
02:08:18,701 --> 02:08:20,216
We have to stop
the bleeding!

1773
02:08:20,217 --> 02:08:21,369
How about my belt?

1774
02:08:21,560 --> 02:08:24,407
- Here Mom!
- Mr. Curtis? Jackson?

1775
02:08:25,694 --> 02:08:27,586
Help! Hey!

1776
02:08:27,619 --> 02:08:29,926
It's Adrian Helmsley,
we met at Yellowstone.

1777
02:08:29,958 --> 02:08:32,443
Thats great. Open
the God damn door!

1778
02:08:32,475 --> 02:08:34,230
Your daughter
is with me!

1779
02:08:34,265 --> 02:08:37,356
- Lilly?
- Where's Noah?

1780
02:08:37,390 --> 02:08:39,146
I'm right here, Lil!

1781
02:08:39,148 --> 02:08:41,037
<i>Impact warning</i>

1782
02:08:41,072 --> 02:08:44,601
<i>30° West.
45° East.</i>

1783
02:08:44,603 --> 02:08:48,270
<i>Target elevation
29.035 feet.</i>

1784
02:08:48,271 --> 02:08:51,409
29.000 feet? What the
hell is at 29.000 feet?

1785
02:08:51,444 --> 02:08:53,173
We're headed straight
for the north face

1786
02:08:53,175 --> 02:08:55,679
of Mount Everest,
Mr. Anheuser.

1787
02:08:55,712 --> 02:08:57,756
And if we can't
start our engines,

1788
02:08:57,757 --> 02:08:59,729
we will not survive
the impact.

1789
02:09:09,488 --> 02:09:12,565
Jackson, you're sealed off!
We can't get to you!

1790
02:09:12,567 --> 02:09:14,414
There's something
blocking the hydraulics

1791
02:09:14,416 --> 02:09:16,992
If you can't get it out,
none of us are gonna make it

1792
02:09:18,029 --> 02:09:20,372
Dr Helmsley,
look at this.

1793
02:09:20,975 --> 02:09:23,100
It's completely submerged
down there and there's

1794
02:09:23,100 --> 02:09:24,698
no way for them
to get any air.

1795
02:09:24,699 --> 02:09:25,877
Theres no other way!

1796
02:09:25,878 --> 02:09:28,168
But it's a suicide
mission, sir!

1797
02:09:35,104 --> 02:09:37,551
I know where it is,
I'll give it a try.

1798
02:09:43,733 --> 02:09:46,219
Dad, wait, I wanna
go with you!

1799
02:09:46,283 --> 02:09:48,836
- Dad, I wanna help you!
- No, no, no.

1800
02:09:48,837 --> 02:09:50,869
- You are helping me.
- Dad, please!

1801
02:09:50,903 --> 02:09:53,284
Remember when Lilly
was born and you wanted

1802
02:09:53,286 --> 02:09:55,359
to be introduced
as her big brother?

1803
02:09:55,514 --> 02:09:56,895
Well, she's scared now.

1804
02:09:56,896 --> 02:09:58,756
She needs you
more than ever.

1805
02:09:58,757 --> 02:10:01,938
If you're safe, I know that
she's safe. Do you understand?

1806
02:10:08,171 --> 02:10:10,181
You can help me out
the next time.

1807
02:10:12,957 --> 02:10:14,877
We caused this thing,
it was us.

1808
02:10:14,878 --> 02:10:16,662
I gotta go
check it out.

1809
02:10:45,662 --> 02:10:47,412
Can you hear me?

1810
02:10:50,742 --> 02:10:52,363
No

1811
02:11:18,141 --> 02:11:19,208
Press down!

1812
02:11:19,242 --> 02:11:21,011
Press down with
your hand!

1813
02:11:28,899 --> 02:11:31,260
Don't stop.
Keep pressing!

1814
02:11:47,291 --> 02:11:50,664
No!

1815
02:11:52,489 --> 02:11:57,117
<i>Distance to impact:
1.850 meters</i>

1816
02:11:59,389 --> 02:12:00,511
There he is!

1817
02:12:02,024 --> 02:12:03,649
- Captain!
- We have a visual!

1818
02:12:03,684 --> 02:12:05,274
I think we found
the problem.

1819
02:12:05,274 --> 02:12:07,273
Show us the
hydraulics chamber

1820
02:12:23,845 --> 02:12:25,809
God dammit! I told you
to stay up there!

1821
02:12:25,810 --> 02:12:27,115
I just wanted to help.

1822
02:12:27,117 --> 02:12:30,328
Alright. Hold the light.

1823
02:12:30,328 --> 02:12:33,033
We're right under
the air pocket, okay?

1824
02:12:33,034 --> 02:12:34,775
How did you know
I needed help?

1825
02:12:39,506 --> 02:12:42,965
Grandpa, Grandma...
I'm sorry.

1826
02:12:42,998 --> 02:12:44,064
I could not save us

1827
02:12:44,435 --> 02:12:47,748
He has gone back in.
He will fix it.

1828
02:12:48,055 --> 02:12:50,668
There's no way.

1829
02:12:51,217 --> 02:12:53,594
Don't lose faith, brother.

1830
02:13:20,252 --> 02:13:21,868
Dad!

1831
02:13:29,003 --> 02:13:30,181
We're gonna die!

1832
02:13:51,524 --> 02:13:54,516
Great job! You light the way
and I'll go for the cable.

1833
02:13:55,676 --> 02:13:58,438
<i>Distance to impact:
400 meters</i>

1834
02:13:58,439 --> 02:13:59,636
Underwater ridge ahead!

1835
02:13:59,636 --> 02:14:01,015
We're going to run
aground, Captain!

1836
02:14:30,114 --> 02:14:31,837
Sir, the gate is sealed!

1837
02:14:31,838 --> 02:14:33,003
That's affirmative, Captain!

1838
02:14:33,005 --> 02:14:36,908
- Anton, start the engines.
- Aye-aye Captain. Full reverse.

1839
02:14:44,336 --> 02:14:46,470
Captain! We're not
gonna make it!

1840
02:14:46,471 --> 02:14:49,500
<i>Distance to impact:
15 meters.</i>

1841
02:15:13,390 --> 02:15:15,583
Reverse motion
activated

1842
02:15:15,585 --> 02:15:19,057
<i>Distance to impact:
10 meters.</i>

1843
02:15:19,703 --> 02:15:21,182
<i>20 meters.</i>

1844
02:15:34,987 --> 02:15:37,317
Hard to port!

1845
02:15:47,949 --> 02:15:50,307
We did it! We did it!

1846
02:15:50,938 --> 02:15:53,288
- Where's Dad?
- He was right behind me

1847
02:15:54,676 --> 02:15:56,788
Any word from the
hydraulic chamber?

1848
02:15:56,789 --> 02:15:57,597
Where is he?

1849
02:15:57,599 --> 02:15:59,280
I thought you said he
was right behind you.

1850
02:15:59,282 --> 02:15:59,952
He was!

1851
02:15:59,953 --> 02:16:01,805
<i>- Are you sure?
- Yes.</i>

1852
02:16:01,805 --> 02:16:03,608
He was right there!

1853
02:16:11,391 --> 02:16:14,706
Dad. Dad!

1854
02:16:14,707 --> 02:16:17,335
Come on, Jackson.
Come on.

1855
02:16:20,908 --> 02:16:23,551
<i>Please, please.</i>

1856
02:16:25,399 --> 02:16:28,038
Please, please.

1857
02:16:44,524 --> 02:16:45,822
He did it!

1858
02:16:46,088 --> 02:16:47,386
He did it!

1859
02:17:30,217 --> 02:17:37,286
DAY 27 MONTH 01 YEAR 0001

1860
02:17:43,561 --> 02:17:46,413
Shuttle Atlantis.
Our last day.

1861
02:17:46,414 --> 02:17:49,809
All we can hear is the sound
of our own breathing.

1862
02:17:49,810 --> 02:17:51,851
That reminds us we are still

1863
02:17:51,886 --> 02:17:55,112
sharing our memories,
hopes and ideas.

1864
02:17:55,113 --> 02:17:58,524
And isn't it funny?
Just this morning we worked it out

1865
02:17:58,525 --> 02:18:01,859
Somehow or another,
we all have relatives

1866
02:18:01,860 --> 02:18:03,479
in Wisconsin.

1867
02:18:05,818 --> 02:18:07,183
The end.

1868
02:18:16,690 --> 02:18:17,879
It's good.

1869
02:18:18,707 --> 02:18:20,325
I thought you
would like it.

1870
02:18:22,201 --> 02:18:27,701
Tell me Dr Wilson:
Apart from books and art.

1871
02:18:27,702 --> 02:18:28,872
Do you think there's
anything else

1872
02:18:28,873 --> 02:18:29,834
we might possibly share?

1873
02:18:31,221 --> 02:18:33,185
In the future?

1874
02:18:34,067 --> 02:18:37,496
Are you asking me out
on a date, Dr. Helmsley?

1875
02:18:38,272 --> 02:18:41,031
You know my diary
is pretty full.

1876
02:18:42,503 --> 02:18:44,048
Actually...

1877
02:18:46,421 --> 02:18:48,120
Yes, I was.

1878
02:18:52,407 --> 02:18:54,877
<i>Dr. Helmsley to
the bridge, please.</i>

1879
02:18:54,878 --> 02:18:57,121
<i>Dr. Helmsley
to the bridge.</i>

1880
02:18:59,248 --> 02:19:00,649
Come here.

1881
02:19:06,835 --> 02:19:09,236
<i>Ladies and gentleman,
this is captain Michaels speaking.</i>

1882
02:19:09,237 --> 02:19:13,163
<i>In a few minutes I will give
orders to unseal the decks.</i>

1883
02:19:14,333 --> 02:19:17,505
<i>At 23:45 last night,
our sister Arks</i>

1884
02:19:17,540 --> 02:19:20,915
<i>number 6 and 7
have joined our course.</i>

1885
02:19:21,595 --> 02:19:23,273
<i>For the first time
on our journey,</i>

1886
02:19:23,274 --> 02:19:24,235
we will have clear skies.

1887
02:19:26,381 --> 02:19:28,358
<i>As you know our
passenger count</i>

1888
02:19:28,359 --> 02:19:29,318
<i>is way over capacity.</i>

1889
02:19:29,945 --> 02:19:32,471
<i>So please, be careful
when you step out</i>

1890
02:19:32,472 --> 02:19:35,697
<i>and of course...
enjoy the fresh air.</i>

1891
02:19:38,372 --> 02:19:39,770
Can I hold him?

1892
02:19:39,771 --> 02:19:42,858
Sure, he can be your
dog too if you like.

1893
02:19:42,859 --> 02:19:44,093
Thanks.

1894
02:19:47,811 --> 02:19:49,260
Where have you
been all my life?

1895
02:19:49,261 --> 02:19:50,701
Gift shop.

1896
02:20:45,610 --> 02:20:47,838
Oh, Adrian. Excellent.

1897
02:20:47,873 --> 02:20:50,938
I called because we just got
our first satellite feet.

1898
02:20:50,939 --> 02:20:53,368
The equalization of the
oceanic... seabeds

1899
02:20:53,369 --> 02:20:55,916
has not turned out to be
as extreme as we expected.

1900
02:20:55,917 --> 02:20:57,754
The waters are receding.

1901
02:20:57,755 --> 02:20:58,805
Much faster
than we thought.

1902
02:20:58,806 --> 02:21:00,662
Thank God. And...

1903
02:21:00,663 --> 02:21:02,913
This is hard to believe,
but the Himalayas

1904
02:21:02,914 --> 02:21:04,813
are no longer the
roof of the world.

1905
02:21:04,814 --> 02:21:06,688
It's now the
Drakensberg mountains

1906
02:21:06,689 --> 02:21:08,000
of KwaZulu, Nepal.

1907
02:21:08,001 --> 02:21:10,352
The entire African
continent has just risen

1908
02:21:10,352 --> 02:21:12,891
7.000 feet, and unlikely
they are even flooded.

1909
02:21:12,893 --> 02:21:15,596
That's why they call it
The Cape of Good Hope.

1910
02:21:15,597 --> 02:21:17,386
We've already set
course for it.

1911
02:21:24,343 --> 02:21:26,686
Daddy, when will
we go back home?

1912
02:21:26,688 --> 02:21:28,103
Well, we talked
about that.

1913
02:21:28,138 --> 02:21:29,520
We're gonna
find a new home

1914
02:21:29,521 --> 02:21:30,479
out here somewhere.

1915
02:21:30,921 --> 02:21:32,111
Right?

1916
02:21:32,111 --> 02:21:34,861
Wherever we're all
together. That's home.

1917
02:21:34,861 --> 02:21:37,280
Right? You are scared?

1918
02:21:37,281 --> 02:21:38,595
I am not.

1919
02:21:40,516 --> 02:21:42,340
No more pull-ups.

1920
02:21:45,004 --> 02:21:46,448
Nice.

